10 March 2022 Members of the media are advised that government Ministers and MECs will host a series of activities ahead of the Presidential Imbizo scheduled to take place in Mahikeng, North West on Saturday, 12 March 2022. The activities include a session between the Minister in Presidency, Mondli Gungubele and Minister of Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs (CoGTA), Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma and the North West Provincial Executive led by Premier, Bushy Maape. The primary objective of this session is to discuss ways and strategies, which can enable the implementation of the District Development Model (DDM). The media programme for the build-up activities scheduled for Friday, 11 March 2022 are as follows and times allocated for media interactions at the various events: MEDIA PROGRAMME Time:      10h25 - 11h00: Keynote address by the Minister       Venue:      Kgora Training Centre, Mahikeng Time:      10h00: interaction with Mafikeng Provincial Hospital Management and       11h35-12h15: Walkabout at Thuthuzela and vaccination centers       Venue: Mafikeng Provincial Hospital MEDIA ACCREDITATION Members of media who have applied for accreditation to cover Presidential Imbizo in Mahikeng, North West Province are advised to collect accreditation cards. Details of collection of media accreditation are as follows: Date: Friday, 11 March 2022Time: 10h00 – 16h00Venue: Disaster Management Centre, Corner Vryburg Road and Rhodes Crescent Road in Empirial Reserve, Mahikeng NB: Members of the media are advised to bring along their Press cards/ ID books when collecting their accreditation cards. Also, note that individuals have to collect their own accreditation at the centre. Enquiries for accreditation should be directed to: Abigail Batala on 078 820 7690 General media enquiries: Brian Setswambung on 076 012 4501 or William Baloyi on 083 390 7147